The '''Dai Bendu''',<ref name="TROS VD" /> also known as the '''Bendu''',<ref name="BMF 25" /> were a [[Religion|religious]] group<ref name="TROS VD" /> that were the precursors of the [[Jedi Order]]. The [[Dai Bendu holocron|first]] [[holocron]]s were attributed to the Dai Bendu. The Order also shared its name<ref name="Unlimited Power">''[[Unlimited Power]]''</ref> with an ancient being known as the [[Bendu]].<ref name="Databank">{{Databank|bendu|Bendu}}</ref>

The [[Republic crest|symbol]] of [[Galactic Republic]] that adorned the [[starfighter]]s of the [[Jedi Knight]]s dated back to the Bendu monks' study of numerology, in which the number nine&mdash;symbolized by eight spokes joined to one disk&mdash;signified the<ref name="BMF 25" /> benevolent<ref name="Complete Vehicles 2018">[[Star Wars: Complete Vehicles (2018)|''Star Wars: Complete Vehicles'' (2018)]]</ref> presence of [[the Force]] in a united [[The galaxy|galaxy]].<ref name="BMF 25" /> In the [[galactic standard calendar]], the fifth and final day of the week "[[Benduday]]" was named for the Bendu monks of the [[planet]] [[Coruscant]].<ref name="BMF 61" />

They constructed a [[Dai Bendu Monastery|monastery]] in what became [[Kijimi City]] on the [[planet]] [[Kijimi]]<ref name="TROS VD" /> around [[965 BBY]].<ref name="Monastery Construction Date">According to ''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker: The Visual Dictionary]]'', the Dai Bendu Monastery was constructed on [[Kijimi]] a [[Millennium|thousand years]] prior to the [[planet]]'s [[Destruction of Kijimi|destruction]] depicted in [[Star Wars: Episode IX The Rise of Skywalker|''Star Wars'': Episode IX ''The Rise of Skywalker'']]. As events of ''The Rise of Skywalker'' took place a [[Standard year|year]] after the [[Hosnian Cataclysm|Starkiller Incident]], as established by ''The Visual Dictionary'', and because ''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]'' states that the Incident occurred in [[34 ABY]], the monastery was constructed around the [[time]] of 965 BBY.</ref> The existence of the temple prompted the [[Brotherhood of the Beatific Countenance]] to make a pilgrimage to Kijimi, inhabiting the [[Thieves' Quarter|Quarter of the Beatific]].<ref name="TROS VD" /> It was believed locally that [[Skordu]] had originally been invented by the Dai Bendu [[monk]]s back when the city was still a religious stronghold.<ref name="TROS Expanded">''[[Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker: Expanded Edition]]''</ref>

After the fall of the Republic and its replacement by the [[Galactic Empire]] in [[19 BBY]],<ref name="Galactic Atlas">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Atlas]]''</ref> the self-appointed [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] Palpatine personalized the ancient icon of the Bendu by removing two spokes, thus creating the [[Imperial crest]].<ref name="BMF 25" />
{{Deity-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Dai Bendu were first mentioned in the new ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in the [[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon 25|twenty-fifth issue]] of the [[De Agostini]] magazine ''[[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon]]'',<ref name="BMF 25" /> published around [[June 24]], [[2015]].<ref name="BMFdates">{{BMFdates|25}}</ref> In [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]], the Dai Bendu are known as the Order of Dai Bendu<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> and they were one of the predecessor organizations to the [[Je'daii Order]]<ref name="DOJ1">[[Dawn of the Jedi: Force Storm 1|''Dawn of the Jedi: Force Storm'' 1]]</ref> alongside the [[Followers of Palawa]] and the [[Chatos Academy]].<ref name="NEC" />

